# Build context for faucet/Dockerfile is the monorepo root (one level up).
# Anything listed here is excluded from the context tarball sent to dockerd.
#
# Per Docker docs (https://docs.docker.com/build/concepts/context/#dockerignore-files),
# BuildKit looks for `<dockerfile-name>.dockerignore` next to the Dockerfile FIRST,
# then falls back to `.dockerignore` at the build context root. This file lives in
# /faucet/ with the standard name `.dockerignore`, which is NEITHER location, so we
# also ship `Dockerfile.dockerignore` as a symlink to this file in the same directory
# — that one IS picked up by BuildKit. The legacy builder (`DOCKER_BUILDKIT=0`) would
# look only at the context root and miss both; require BuildKit (default since 23.0).

# Per-package
node_modules
.next
data
.env.faucet
*.log
tsconfig.tsbuildinfo

# Workspace-wide (with build context = repo root, dockerd would otherwise ship
# every node_modules tree across the monorepo — hundreds of MB and obviously
# wrong because the Dockerfile installs fresh inside the build stage).
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/dist
**/.turbo
**/.cache
**/tsconfig.tsbuildinfo
**/coverage
**/.aztec-store
**/.aztec-pxe-*

# Git + IDE + OS noise
.git
.github
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store

# Foundry / Noir build artifacts (regenerated by `pnpm compile`; the only
# artifact we DO need — contracts/*/target/*.json — slips through this rule
# only because Foundry's `contracts-l1/out/` is the directory we're hiding,
# not `contracts/*/target/`. The Noir target/ JSONs are kept.)
contracts-l1/out
contracts-l1/cache
contracts-l1/lib
contracts-l1/broadcast

# Runtime / per-operator state (never bake into an image)
.env.testnet
testnet-*-state.json
testnet-*-pxe
testnet-sub6-state.json
testnet-sub6b-*-state.json
testnet-sub6b-*-pxe
testnet-pool-state-*.json
deploy-bridge-state.json
quetzal.config.json
quetzal.config.*-backup.json
wallet_data_*
aggregator/snapshots
codegenCache.json

# Vercel local linkage (irrelevant to the Docker image)
.vercel
.vercelignore

# NOTE: we deliberately do NOT exclude `frontend/`, even though the faucet has
# no runtime dependency on it, because the Dockerfile's deps stage runs
# `COPY frontend/package.json` to give pnpm visibility of every workspace
# member (otherwise `pnpm install` errors with "package.json not found"). The
# frontend/node_modules + frontend/dist are excluded above via **/node_modules
# + **/dist, which is what matters for context size.
